default  
defaultIt is well know
defaultn
default that people from ethnic minorities are over-represe
defaultnted in the prison population. 
defaultOn 31 March 2013, 26% of the prison population, 21,462 prisoners, was from a minority ethnic group.
default This compares to around one in 10 of the general population.
default&#xa0;
defaultThere are also a disproportionate number of disabled people i
defaultn prisons compared to the general population.
default defaultThis is harder to estimate
default:
default nevertheless, an estimate
defaultd
default 36% of prisoners interviewed in a Ministry of Justice study were considered to have a disability when answers about disability and health, including mental health, were screened.
default 
